---
title: No-Chop Ancho Mango Shrimp Bowls No knife work & only one pot!
description: Our easiest-ever meals with no knifework and only one pot, done in a flash! For these flavor-packed sweet-heat bowls, you’ll sauté shrimp, then toss with microwavable rice and tangy-sweet mangos. Add our mildly spicy ancho sauce made with roasted onions and earthy ancho chiles, and dinner’s on the table in under 15 minutes!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67e12c007594446a7cdcbac8-31965ac6.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67e12c007594446a7cdcbac8-en-US.pdf
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/no-chop-ancho-mango-shrimp-bowls-67e12c007594446a7cdcbac8
time required: 10 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 1 g
  sodium: 1330 mg
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
---

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water and pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, turning occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Massage @microwavable rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for shrimp over medium-high heat. Add rice to pan and season with salt and pepper. Add @water{1/4%cup} and @mango{4%ounce}(with juice); stir to combine. Cook, stirring frequently, until rice is warmed through and liquid has reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

  > Use 1/2 cup water for 4 servings.

Remove pan from heat; stir in @zesty ancho sauce{3%ounce} and half the shrimp. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide shrimp and rice between #bowls{}. Top with remaining shrimp and serve.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.